The paper discusses the design and implementation of efficient algorithms for collective operations in MPI on systems with multiple communication networks or multiple connections to the network. This topic falls under the categories of distributed computing (cs.DC), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and parallel computing (cs.PF). The paper also discusses self-consistent performance guidelines and the conversion of standard communication tree algorithms into multi-lane algorithms, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
